webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Gulnat photograph of older man. According to the papacy, the father of the ferry master and the councilor in Lköpping, Oskar Andersson (1845-1925). Is this the name of the man Anders Eriksson, married to Anna Jansdotter. The couple was home owner of Ullnäs, Örberga parish at the time of the son’s birth. Already in 1848, the family is housed in a backhut under the Örberga murgård. The decay escalates. From 1851 the family is without a permanent residence, they are as the sources call it “written on the parish.” Anders is also convicted of theft. He died as a widower in 1862 - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMEA0001240030. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021017436668. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
